<dl id="n36207a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36207a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36207a"> 207(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lubbereator</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Ku Kluxism.]</font> The Klan is no mere agency with a lofty purpose, but an instrument in the hands of God. The patriots which comprise it are &ldquo;not only <mark>custodians of liberty</mark>, but of the whole social and moral structure, involving both politics and religion.&rdquo; <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 274</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09116b" href="c09all.htm#c09116b">VI.C.09:116(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
